y significant radiation at all. Apparently one of the requirements for the R-54s was that the little bombs be as clean as possible. The tactical reason was that our troops wouldn’t be required to hump through HOT areas on their way to their objectives or be forced to occupy and defend HOT city streets. The ultra clean burn was accomplished via tritium boosting that kicks up the density of slow neutrons and thus causes the fuel to burn more completely.<br>
<br>
 I guess that puts a cork in the mouths of the tree huggers who believe that a ground launched ORION would leave a trail of deadly sizzling fallout in its wake…..what am I saying the anti nuke clowns NEVER let the facts get in the way of their mindless bombast.<br>
